"&#xa0;\nWritten evidence from Gary Sullivan (CYS0024)&#xa0;Executive Summary&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;Introduction&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\nOverview on the use of Consolidation Centres in the UK Construction Sector&#xa0;&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\nThere have been specific project CC’s which will be referred to in this evidence.\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n“T5 was planned and delivered as a logistics project first and construction project second” Shaun Cowlam, Head of Logistics\n,\n BAA.\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\nThe headlines from the final report \n(TfL\n et al, Oct \n2008\n) showed many improvements in reliability (97% versus 39%), efficiency and safety. The report stated that in \nthe pilot study period of 2 years and involving\n 4 projects totalling 80,000 \nSq m\n of office space, the use of the LCCC prevent\ned 3,000 vehicles entering the Congestion Charge Z\none. \n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\nConclusions and recommendations&#xa0;&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\nNovember 2013\n&#xa0;\nReferences&#xa0;\nConstructing Excellence, 2004, ‘Models for Consolidation’, \nhttp://www.wilsonjames.co.uk/files/PUBLIC/Construction/PDFs/Constructing_Excellence_%20Models_For_Consolidation_October_2004.pdf\n&#xa0;\nDepartment of Trade &amp; Industry, 2004, ‘Construction Logistics Consolidation Centres’, \nhttp://www.wilsonjames.co.uk/files/PUBLIC/Construction/PDFs/DtI_%20Executive_Summary_Report_Construction_\nLogistics_Consolidation_Centres_October_2004.pdf\n&#xa0;\nEarthshine, 2010, ‘\nWilson James: Driving Efficiency, Value\n \nand Sustainability in the Supply Chain\n’, \nhttp://www.wilsonjames.co.uk/files/PUBLIC/Construction/PDFs/Earthshine_Driving_Efficiency_Value_and_Sustainability_in_the_Supply_Chain_2010.pdf\n&#xa0;\nTransport for London et al, 2008, ‘London Construction\n Consolidation Centre’, \nhttp://www.wilsonjames.co.uk/files/PUBLIC/Construction/PDFs/TfL_LCCC_final_report_July_2009.pdf\n&#xa0;\nWRAP, 2010, ‘Central St\n Giles: Stanhope, Bovis Lend Lease and Wilson James’, \nhttp://www.wilsonjames.co.uk/files/PUBLIC/Construction/PDFs/WRAP_Central_St_Giles_March_2010\n.pdf\n&#xa0;\nBiography of Submission Author, Gary Sullivan OBE&#xa0;\nCareer Summary&#xa0;\nGary specialises in Construction Logistics, supply chain development and regeneration.  He has over 20 years \nof \nexperience in the planning and operation of the logistics of \ncomplex infrastructure projects. Gary has been involved with many high profile projects with BAA, AWE, BBC, MOD and the Olympics.\n&#xa0;\nIn addition to developing the UK’s foremost security and logistics contractor, from a standing start, to recognised industry \nleader, Gary has served in the Parachute Regiment and worked for the United Nations High Commissioner for Refugees. He was commissioned into the Engineer and Logistics Staff Corps in 2011.\n&#xa0;\nGary was awarded an OBE in Queen’s Birthday Honours List in June 2\n012 for Service to Regeneration of the Thames Gateway, and in October 2012 he received an Honorary Doctorate from Anglia Ruskin University in Business Administration.  He is a published author and a UNICEF Global Guardian.\n&#xa0;\nExecutive Positions&#xa0;\n2011\n              \n              \nChair\nman, Wilson James Ltd\n1994 - 2011\n              \nManaging Director, Wilson James Ltd\n1992 - 1993\n              \nSenior Logistics &amp; Transport Advisor, UNHCR\n1988 - 1992\n              \nSecurity &amp; Logistics Executive, Stanhope\n1979 – 1988\n              \nBritish Army\n&#xa0;\nNon-Executive Positions&#xa0;\n2013\n              \n              \nChairman of Active E\nssex\n2008 - 2012\n              \nChairman of Essex Olympic Strategic Board for Legacy, \n              \n              \nChairman of Planning Safety Advisory Group, Torch Relay\n2005 - 2008\n              \nBoard Member Sport England East\n2004 - 2012\n              \nChairman, Thames Gateway South Essex Partnership\n2003 - 2011\n              \nBoard Member Renaissance Southend\n2000 - 2005\n              \nChairman, Business Link for Essex\n&#xa0;\nEducation&#xa0;\nAnglia Ruskin University - MBA (2002)\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n"